707278f-b.text:
(1)
WTarwick Street, east side, south of Dumont Ave., showing the barns and home of William Hopkins. Most of these buildings were demolished prioh to 1908. If the house were standing now (1937) it would occupy a triangular plot of ground bounded by Warwick and Ashford Streets. Livonia and New Lots Aves., on the west, east, north and south respectively. (This information obtained from Bear's "Long Island Atlas
of 1873).
About 1895.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, from a different angle.
About 1895.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
